he strength of rail administration. Pragmatic management, combining central authority and local autonomy, sustained rail organizations amid shifting political and economic priorities. As Köll shows, rail provided a blueprint for the past forty years of ambitious, semipublic business development and remains an essential component of the PRC’s politically charged, technocratic economic model for China’s future.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aInfrastructure (Economics)zChina. 0aRailroads and statezChinaxHistory. 0aRailroadszChinaxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Asia / China.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHarvard University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065203140uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/978067491641840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674916418423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780674916418/original  a978-3-11-065203-1  Harvard University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles